Amber: I won’t judge Master Otto for what he’s done, but history will.

Amber: I hope… in the near future, you can keep it in the Schicksal Museum.

Amber: At that time, people can reach their own conclusions on the life of Otto Apocalypse based on the various exhibits.

Amber: That might be my insistence as his secretary.

Theresa: …Fine. I don’t quite understand what you said though.

Theresa: But what you said is not meant to be understood here and now, right?

Amber didn’t answer. She made a bow and turned to leave.

Theresa: Wait, Amber!

Amber: What is it, Master Theresa?

Theresa: I know our allegiances don’t exactly align right now.

Theresa: But still, I hope you’ll find your own path.

Amber: …

Amber: I see. Thank you, Master Theresa.

Amber smiled gently and nodded at Theresa with respect before she took leave.

